explanation: No additional symbols are required. The MISRA rule in question applies to for-statements; OS_API_Impl_Init contains no for loop (only a call to OS_Posix_TableMutex_Init, a switch, and calls in case branches). Therefore there is no for-statement in the target function whose three clauses or loop counter behavior must be checked. To be complete: if a for-loop existed in this function (or if a for-loop were introduced that called other functions), you would need the source (or prototypes) of any called functions and any global/extern objects referenced or modified by the loop body to determine side-effects. In this specific case none of those additional symbols are needed to decide compliance.
